    FROM

    JOIN 
        atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
),
ElementPairCounts AS (
    SELECT 
        element1, 
        element2, 
        COUNT(*) AS pair_count
    FROM 
        ElementPairs
    GROUP BY 
        element1, 
        element2
),
MostCommonPair AS (
    SELECT 
        element1, 
        element2
    FROM 
        ElementPairCounts
    ORDER BY 
        pair_count DESC
    LIMIT 1
),

    SELECT 
        c.bond_id
    FROM 
        connected c
    JOIN 
        atom a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
    JOIN 
        atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
    JOIN 
        MostCommonPair mcp ON a1.element = mcp.element1 AND a2.element = mcp.element2

        y.Consumption,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY c.Segment ORDER BY y.Consumption ASC) as rn
    FROM 
        customers c
    JOIN 
        yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        y.Date LIKE '2013%' 
        AND c.Currency = 'CZK'
),
SegmentAverages AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        SUM(Consumption) * 1.0 / COUNT(CustomerID) as AvgConsumption
    FROM 
        LowestConsumption
    WHERE 
        rn = 1
    GROUP BY 
        Segment
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'SME') - 
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'LAM') AS SME_LAM,
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'LAM') - 
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'KAM') AS LAM_KAM,
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'KAM') - 
    (SELECT AvgConsumption FROM SegmentAverages WHERE Segment = 'SME') AS KAM_SME

WITH AggregatedConsumption AS (
    SELECT 
        c.Segment,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2012%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2012,
        SUM(CASE WHEN y.Date LIKE '2013%' THEN y.Consumption ELSE 0 END) AS Consumption_2013
    FROM 
        customers c
    JOIN 
        yearmonth y ON c.CustomerID = y.CustomerID
    WHERE 
        c.Currency = 'EUR'
    GROUP BY 
        c.Segment
),
PercentageIncrease AS (
    SELECT 
        Segment,
        ((Consumption_2013 - Consumption_2012) * 1.0 / Consumption_2013) * 100 AS Percentage_Increase
    FROM 
        AggregatedConsumption
    WHERE 
        Consumption_2013 <> 0
)
SELECT 
    (SELECT Segment FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY Percentage_Increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS Biggest_Increase_Segment,
    (SELECT Segment FROM PercentageIncrease ORDER BY Percentage_Increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS Lowest_Increase_Segment;
